In a statement on the passing of Fidel Castro, the President of the United States extended a hand of friendship to the Cuban people. He acknowledged the powerful emotions that this moment brings to Cubans in both Cuba and the United States, recognizing the impact that Castro had on individual lives, families, and the Cuban nation. The statement highlighted the history of discord and political disagreements between the US and Cuba, but also emphasized the efforts made during the President's tenure to move towards a future defined by common bonds and engagement. The President offered condolences to Castro's family and expressed support for the Cuban people, assuring them of the friendship and partnership of the United States.